<title>NORWAY: Statoil completes Heidrun repairs.</title>
<headline>Statoil completes Heidrun repairs.</headline>
<dateline>OSLO 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Two flare burners on the Heidrun platform in the Norwegian Sea were replaced last week during a four-hour operation, operator Den norsle stats oljeselskap AS (Statoil) said on Thursday.</p>
<p>The repairs were required after one of the tips broke off last October, causing a brief shutdown in production.</p>
<p>Statoil's Status Weekly newsletter said a new ignition system for gas, which must be flared for safety reasons, meant that a pilot light no longer had to burn continuously on the flare.</p>
<p>It said the 250,000 barrel per day Heidrun field now had a system for reusing flare gas.</p>
<p>-- Tanya Pang, Oslo newsroom, +47 22 42 50 41</p>
